  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6856.37 trading just above the GEX flip at 6839 and approaching the massive +8703M gamma wall at 6850, dealers are actively selling into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions. The strong PIN regime with 63.9B in total GEX creates significant resistance at the 6850 strike, where dealers will aggressively sell any push higher, while the layered positive gamma walls at 6900/7000 form additional ceiling levels. Given spot is sandwiched between the flip point and max gamma strike with decent upward momentum (+0.6% 1-min, +0.8% 5-min), expect initial resistance at 6850 but potential for a grind toward 6875-6900 if buying pressure persists, though dealers will fade any strength above these levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect selling pressure to cap gains near 6850 with choppy action between 6840-6860.",
